# CODEOWNERS for the ready-suite hub.
#
# This file routes pull-request review automatically. The current maintainer
# is @aihxp; that line below covers everything by default. Path-specific
# rules below the default exist to make the high-blast-radius surfaces
# explicit, so a future co-maintainer can see at a glance which files
# trigger which reviewers.
#
# When a second maintainer is added, replace `@aihxp` on the load-bearing
# rules below with `@aihxp @second-maintainer-handle` so PRs touching
# those paths require both reviewers.

# Default fallback: hub maintainer reviews everything.
* @aihxp

# SUITE.md is byte-identical across all 12 repos. A change here cascades.
# Reviewer must verify the lint runs green and the sync to siblings is
# part of the same coordinated patch.
/SUITE.md @aihxp

# ORCHESTRATORS.md lives in hub + production-ready (not byte-identical
# across the full suite, but mirrored at a 2-repo cadence). Updates here
# need to mirror to production-ready in the same patch.
/ORCHESTRATORS.md @aihxp

# Install/uninstall scripts touch every consumer's filesystem. Bash 3.2
# regressions, harness-detection mistakes, and ~/.agents/skills path
# decisions all break user installs silently. High-blast surface.
/install.sh @aihxp
/uninstall.sh @aihxp

# Meta-linter mechanically enforces suite discipline. A check that fails
# to fail (or fails when it should not) silently degrades the protection
# the suite has against drift.
/scripts/ @aihxp

# CI workflows. A workflow regression cascades to every push.
/.github/workflows/ @aihxp

# Trigger disambiguation table. Adding a row is fine; removing or
# rewriting a row changes the canonical answer to a routing question.
/references/TRIGGER-DISAMBIGUATION.md @aihxp

# Plugin marketplace manifest. A manifest typo breaks Claude Code's
# `/plugin install` command for every consumer.
/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json @aihxp
